Users of Equity Group&rsquo;s mobile money platform, Equitel, can buy airtime via their M-Pesa accounts, the company announced yesterday, putting an end to a two-year feud between Equity and Safaricom.The partnership is expected to boost the revenue of the two firms at the time convergence between technology and banking is taking shape, bringing efficiency to consumers. Equitel subscribers can now covert idle cash balances on their M-Pesa accounts into airtime for their Equitel lines using a new paybill number issued by Safaricom without incurring transaction charges for airtime purchases below Sh100The launch of Equitel two years ago through a partnership between Equity Bank and Airtel was seen by many analysts a threat to Safaricom&rsquo;s diverse communication and money services.